The paper deals with the optimization of data representation for interactive multiview navigation, which involves 3D scenes and navigation through them. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Multimedia (cs.MM), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Graphics (cs.GR), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Modeling and Simulation (cs.MS). Among these, Multimedia and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition seem to be the most likely categories, as they deal with image and video processing, which are relevant to the paper's focus on visual quality and compression performance. Graphics and Modeling and Simulation are also relevant, as they deal with 3D scenes and navigation, but may be less likely as they are more focused on the creation and simulation of virtual environments rather than the optimization of data representation. Information Theory is also relevant, as it deals with the trade-offs between data compression and transmission, but may be less likely as it is more focused on theoretical aspects of data representation rather than practical applications.
